erta.ca/content/doctype353/production/NEAHDbridgesummary.pdf <!--|page=9--> |title=North East Edmonton Ring Road Advanced Functional Plan - Bridge Planning Summary Report |date=March 2010 |accessdate=2016-10-14 |df=mdy-all |page=87 (of PDF) |format=PDF |work=ISL Engineering and Land Services}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ITS>{{Cite web | url=http://www.transportation.alberta.ca/Content/docType52/Production/RRStudyTOR.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101205000914/http://www.transportation.alberta.ca/Content/docType52/Production/RRStudyTOR.pdf |archivedate=2010-12-05 |date=2004-03-01 |df=mdy-all |title=Intelligent Transportation Systems Study for the Edmonton and Calgary Ring Roads |publisher=Alberta Transportation |url-status=live |page=2 |quote=AHD is part of Alberta Transportation's initiative to provide a high standard highway trade corridor linking Alberta to the United States and Mexico. In addition, the roadway forms an important part of Edmonton's overall transportation system and is included in the City's Transportation Master Plan..}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Lafarge>{{Cite web |url=http://www.lafargeinfrastructure.ca/Roadways.aspx |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220000500/http://www.lafargeinfrastructure.ca/Roadways.aspx |accessdate=2016-12-20 |archivedate=2016-12-20 |publisher=Lafarge Infrastructure |title=Roadways |url-status=live |df=mdy-all |quote=Lafarge Infrastructure is responsible for the operations and maintenance of the West, South, and East legs of Anthony Henday Drive Ring Road.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=mx>{{Cite web |url=https://www.transportation.alberta.ca/610.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161207195631/https://www.transportation.alberta.ca/610.htm |date=2016 |archivedate=2016-12-07 |accessdate=2016-12-07 |publisher=Alberta Transportation |df=mdy-all |url-status=live |title=Ring Roads - Edmonton & Calgary |quote=Anthony Henday Drive... used both conventional (SW) delivery and public-private partnership (P3) delivery (SE/