442/http://www.canadianconsultingengineer.com/features/three-crossings-on-henday/ |archivedate=2016-12-07 |df=mdy-all |date=2008-01-01 |url-status=live |accessdate=2016-12-07 |work=Canadian Consulting Engineer |author=Associated Engineering |title=Three Crossings On Henday}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=trellisview>{{Cite web | url=https://goo.gl/maps/FNPCm7yjH4L2 | author=[[Google]] | work=Google Street View | date=September 2015 |title=\"Trellis Beam\" structure over Calgary Trail in Edmonton|accessdate=2016-12-07 | df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=TUC>{{cite web |url=http://www.infrastructure.alberta.ca/TUCContent/Infoe.pdf |title=Transportation/Utility Corridors |year=2009 |publisher=Government of Alberta |accessdate=2016-10-07 |df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=parclo>{{cite web |url=https://www.massdot.state.ma.us/Portals/8/docs/designGuide/CH_7.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214035458/https://www.massdot.state.ma.us/Portals/8/docs/designGuide/CH_7.pdf |archivedate=2016-12-14 |publisher=[[Massachusetts Department of Transportation]] (MassDOT) |pages=14\u201315 |title=Project Development and Design Guide (Chapter 7)|date=January 2006 |accessdate=2016-12-14 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all |quote=However, [cloverleaf] interchanges introduce several undesirable operational features such as double exits and entrances from the mainline, weaving between entering and exiting vehicles, lengthy travel time and distance for left-turning vehicles, and large amounts of required right-of-way.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Ramsay2>{{cite web|url=http://globalnews.ca/news/3436296/110kmh-speed-limit-on-anthony-henday-drive-edmonton-police-chief-supports-the-idea/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509005553/http://globalnews.ca/news/3436296/110kmh-speed-limit-on-anthony-henday-drive-edmonton-police-chief-supports-the-idea/ |archivedate=2017-05-09 |date=2017-05-08 |last=Ramsay |first=Caley |title=110km/h speed limit on Anthony Henday Drive? Edmonton police chief supports the idea |work=Global News |accessdate=2017-05-11 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=sprawl>For a 2012 report analyzing the construction of infrastructure near the outskirts of the city, see {{Cite web|url=http://edmonton.ctvnews.ca/urban-sprawl-to-cost-city-1-2-billion-report-1.807858 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015045616/http://edmonton.ctvnews.ca/urban-sprawl-to-cost-city-1-2-billion-report-1.807858 |archivedate=October 15, 2016 |accessdate=2016-10-15 |date=2012-05-10 |title=Urban sprawl to cost city $1.2 billion: report |work=CTV News |last=Hoang |first=Linda |quote=...there has been an increased [real estate] interest in areas on the fringes of the city. Urban sprawl... is set to cost the city $1.2 billion, according to a new report... |df=mdy-all |url-status=live }}\n*For a 2016 report, see {{Cite web|url=http://www.metronews.ca/news/edmonton/2016/03/17/edmonton-sprawl-will-cost-billion-more-.html |title=Edmonton sprawl will cost $1.4 billion more than it will bring in |author=Tumilty, Ryan |date=2016-03-17 |accessdate=2016-10-15 |url-status=unfit |work=Edmonton Metro News |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318034739/http://www.metronews.ca/news/edmonton/2016/03/17/edmonton-sprawl-will-cost-billion-more-.html |archivedate=March 18, 2016 |df=mdy-all }}\n*For a debate regarding the use of [[infill]], see {{Cite web|title=Infill debate continues to rage in west Edmonton neighbourhood |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/edmonton/infill-debate-continues-to-rage-in-west-edmonton-neighbourhood-1.3511340 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160405131443/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/edmonton/infill-debate-continues-to-rage-in-west-edmonton-neighbourhood-1.3511340 |archivedate=April 5, 2016 |work=CBC News |url-status=live |quote=Graham said infills are used to increase the density in neighbourhoods in an attempt to combat urban sprawl. He believes that Edmonton is taking responsible action by pushing for these developments. \