mont.html |title=Province looks at expanding Highway 2 between Calgary and Edmonton |work=Metro News|archivedate=2016-11-18 |df=mdy-all |date=2015-10-01 |accessdate=2016-11-18 |url-status=unfit |last1=Pike |first1=Helen |last2=Tumilty |first2=Ryan |quote=Highways typically get an expansion to between six or eight lanes when volumes reach between 30,000 and 50,000 cars per day, the [Alberta Transportation] document states.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Wilson>{{Cite web |url=http://www.biographi.ca/en/bio/henday_anthony_3E.html |title=Henday, Anthony | last=Wilson |first=Clifford|date=2003 | website=Dictionary of Canadian Biography |accessdate=2016-10-07 |archive-date=2016-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815225634/http://biographi.ca/en/bio/henday_anthony_3E.html|url-status=live |df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=yellowfund>{{Cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221011655/http://globalnews.ca/news/3131193/federal-funding-expected-to-be-announced-for-edmontons-yellowhead-trail/ |archivedate=December 21, 2016 |url-status=live |url=http://globalnews.ca/news/3131193/federal-funding-expected-to-be-announced-for-edmontons-yellowhead-trail/ |title=Feds throw funding towards Edmonton's Yellowhead Trail project |date=2016-12-16 |last=Kornik |first=Slav |publisher=Global News |accessdate=2016-12-16 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Attached KML|display=title,inline}}\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.transportation.alberta.ca/1701.htm Alberta Transportation - Edmonton Ring Road]\n*[http://www.northeastanthonyhenday.com/ Capital City Link Group - Northeast Anthony Henday Drive]\n\n{{Streets in Edmonton}}\n{{Alberta Provincial Highways|Hwy=yes}}\n\n[[Category:Freeways in Alberta]]\n[[Category:Ring roads in Canada]]\n[[Category:Roads in Edmonton]]\n[[Category:Roads in St. Albert, Alberta]]\n[[Category:Sherwood Park]]\n[[Category:Strathcona County]]\n", "name_user": "NorthwestPassage", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eLane Coun